Introduction

UNI.T was a South Korean project girl group formed through the KBS survival show THE UNIT. The group consisted of nine idols from various agencies and backgrounds: Jiwon (SPICA), Woohee (Dal Shabet), Yoonjo (former member of Hello Venus), Jinyea (LABOUM), NC.A (soloist under Isam Media), Hezz (SONAMOO), Yebin (DIA), Hyunjoo (former member of APRIL), and Suji (The Ark). They made their official debut on May 18, 2018, with the mini album 'LINE.'

The group promoted for five months until their contracts expired on October 12, 2018.
